{
  "local_port": 56532,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best recipes for small batch chocolate chip cookies?",
  "response": "Here are a few delicious small batch chocolate chip cookie recipes that make about 6-12 cookies. Perfect for satisfying a sweet tooth without the temptation of a full batch!\n\n### Classic Small Batch Chocolate Chip Cookies\n\n#### Ingredients\n- 1/4 cup (1/2 stick) unsalted butter, softened\n- 1/4 cup brown sugar, packed\n- 1 tablespoon granulated sugar\n- 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1/8 teaspoon baking soda\n- Pinch of salt\n- 1/2 cup all-purpose flour\n- 1/4 cup chocolate chips\n\n#### Instructions\n1. Preheat your oven to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C) and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.\n2. In a bowl, cream together the softened butter, brown sugar, and granulated sugar until smooth.\n3. Mix in the vanilla extract, baking soda, and salt.\n4. Gradually add the flour and stir until just combined. Fold in the chocolate chips.\n5. Scoop tablespoon-sized balls of dough onto the prepared baking sheet, spacing them about 2 inches apart.\n6. Bake for 8-10 minutes, or until the edges are lightly golden. The centers may look slightly underbaked, but they will continue to set as they cool.\n7. Allow to cool on the baking sheet for a few minutes before transferring to a wire rack.\n\n---\n\n### Chewy Small Batch Chocolate Chip Cookies\n\n#### Ingredients\n- 3 tablespoons unsalted butter, melted\n- 1/4 cup brown sugar, packed\n- 1 tablespoon granulated sugar\n- 1/4 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- Pinch of salt\n- 1/4 teaspoon baking soda\n- 1/4 cup + 1 tablespoon all-purpose flour\n- 1/4 cup chocolate chips\n\n#### Instructions\n1. Preheat the oven to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C) and prepare a baking sheet with parchment paper.\n2. In a mixing bowl, whisk together the melted butter, brown sugar, and granulated sugar until smooth.\n3. Stir in the vanilla extract and salt.\n4. Add the baking soda and flour; mix until just combined. Fold in the chocolate chips.\n5. Scoop dough onto the baking sheet, forming about 6 cookies.\n6. Bake for 8-10 minutes, until the edges are set but the centers remain soft.\n7. Let cool slightly before enjoying!\n\n---\n\n### Gluten-Free Small Batch Chocolate Chip Cookies\n\n#### Ingredients\n- 2 tablespoons coconut oil or unsalted butter, melted\n- 2 tablespoons brown sugar, packed\n- 1 tablespoon granulated sugar\n- 1/4 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- Pinch of salt\n- 1/4 teaspoon baking soda\n- 1/4 cup gluten-free all-purpose flour (with xanthan gum)\n- 2 tablespoons chocolate chips\n\n#### Instructions\n1. Preheat the oven to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C) and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.\n2. In a bowl, mix the melted coconut oil or butter with brown sugar and granulated sugar until smooth.\n3. Stir in the vanilla extract and salt.\n4. Add the baking soda and gluten-free flour; mix until just combined. Fold in the chocolate chips.\n5. Drop tablespoon-sized balls of dough onto the baking sheet.\n6. Bake for 8-10 minutes until the edges are golden and the centers are soft.\n7. Cool slightly before devouring!\n\n---\n\nThese recipes yield a small number of cookies and are perfect for a quick treat! Enjoy baking!",
